Class BindingValue

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--jess.Value
        |
        +--jess.BindingValue
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class BindingValue
extends Value
implements java.io.Serializable

A class to represent a location within a rule LHS, used internally. It is 'self-resolving' using Context. You shouldn't need to use this directly except the implement an Accelerator.

(C) 2003 E.J. Friedman-Hill and the Sandia Corporation
$Id: BindingValue.java,v 1.6 2003/02/05 02:18:07 ejfried Exp $

public jess.Value resolveValue(jess.Context c)
                        throws JessException
Description copied from class: Value
Given an evaluation context, return the "true value" of this Value. For this class, the true value is always "this". For subclasses, the Context may be used to compute a new Value.
